				<h3 id="post-834"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2009/10/08/eight/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Eight."><span class='p-name'>Eight.</span></a></h3>
				<small>Thursday, October 8th, 2009</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class='e-content'><p>Sad news from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hal_Finney_%28cypherpunk%29" rel="tag">Hal Finney</a>, diagnosed with ALS. I&#8217;ve only <a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2005/02/12/codecon-friday/">met</a> him briefly, but have been <a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2006/11/22/bias-enumeration/">following</a> his writing, mostly on mailing lists, for nearly two decades. Very few if any people exist whose thoughts I trust and respect as much as his.</p>
<p>Titled <em><a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ab/dying_outside/">Dying Outside</a></em>, Finney&#8217;s post about his diagnosis, is a fine example of his writing, <a href="http://lists.extropy.org/pipermail/extropy-chat/2004-November/011224.html">for the future</a>.</p>
<p><small><a href="http://www.overcomingbias.com/2009/10/fear-of-near-death-thoughts.html">Via Robin Hanson.</a></small></p>
</div>				</div>

